      <h2>Types of Performance Testing</h2>
      <div class="types-grid">
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Load Testing</h3>
          <p>Evaluate the system under expected user loads to identify potential slowdowns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Stress Testing</h3>
          <p>Push the system beyond its limits to determine its breaking point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Spike Testing</h3>
          <p>Assess the system's behavior under sudden and extreme traffic surges.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Endurance Testing</h3>
          <p>Test the system over a prolonged period to reveal memory leaks or degradation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Scalability Testing</h3>
          <p>Determine how well your system scales as user load increases.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="type-card reveal">
          <h3>Volume Testing</h3>
          <p>Evaluate performance with large data sets or a high number of transactions.</p>
        </div>
